<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:53PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Catawba, Lincoln, southwestern Iredell, northwestern Mecklenburg and
northeastern Gaston Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 453 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Newton, moving south at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Newton, Lincolnton, Huntersville, Conover, Maiden, Westport,
Claremont, Catawba, High Shoals and Lake Norman.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
